default2.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhat are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable? 
default&#xa0;
default2.6.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultS
defaultervice integration 
defaultand 
defaultcross-sector benefits
default:
default  
defaultChallenges presented by the lack of integrated p
defaultlanning are detailed above.  There needs to be a requirement on all publicly funded services to assess the impact of their planning and service provision in order to consider how they can integrate with other sectors.  It is also important that the real co
defaultst of service provision is recognised insofar as those using or procuring services (particularly when this is done indirectly) meet the full and realistic cost of the service which they are receiving.
default&#xa0;
default2.6.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBrokerage and
default 
defaultshare
defaultd resources
default:
default  
defaultThe default position for all publicly funded services/operators/vehicles is that they 
defaultshould 
defaultbe shared and accessible to the maximum number of people unless it can be shown that there is a real and pressing reason for this not to happen.  In isolated commu
defaultnities, it is particularly important that scare resources are effectively utilised.  There is no reason why NHS, local authority, school or CT vehicles cannot be used to help meet the needs of groups other the
defaultir
default core clients.
default&#xa0;
default2.6.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFull cost recovery
default for voluntary car schemes
default:
default  Hundreds (possibly thousands) of car schemes operate across the country.  Transport authorities and the NHS frequently make use of these services to support the delivery of their statutory obligations.  This engagement needs to
default be more formally recognised and statutory agencies must pay the full cost of the services/benefits they are receiving.
